review_blob: The best thing I can say about this one is that I didnt die after drinking it.  Anheuser-Busch better be happy that Michelob Ultra came out and replaced this as the worst beer in the world.
Well, it has this going for it, its better than Bud Light, Natural Light, Corona Light, and Michelob Ultra.  Other than that nothing.  If you must drink light beer this wont kill you.
I prefer Guinness Draught to this but this is also an acceptable alternative.  More bitter than Draught and less carbonation too.
I kind of come and go on this but right now i really like this beer.  The more i have the more i like it.  Good bitter flavor, but not too harsh.
Not too impressed. Had this one just after having an Icehouse and still wasnt impressed.  Figure that may be a decent sign of mediocrity.
Pleasent and refreshing are the two best deScriptors.  Clean finish too.  No real complaints to be had here.
Very interesting brew here.  Sam Adams has many other alternatives that are much better.  But drinking this is not totally absurd.  Not the biggest fruit beer fan though.
When going somewhere that serves Miller, Bud, Coors you can usually get this which is better.  Little use besides that though.
In the same leauge as heineken but better.  Most notable feature is the interesting bottles.  That alone makes it more worthwhile than Heine.
Pours a gorgeous reddish color.  Aroma and taste slightly of caramel.  A worthwhile effort from Coors which is more than can be said of most of their crap.
Excellent nutty flavor.  Great aroma too.  Wide availability is also a plus.  Worth while for a try for sure.
Definitely a good choice.  A nice deep amber color and a definite hops presence in the taste.  Very enjoyable and I would defnitely reccommend it.
Copper color.  Not that strong of a taste.  Definitely many better bocks out there than this one.  Too watery.
An admirable effort from michelob considering the rest of their product line.  I have to give them credit for making at least one worthwhile beer.
Definite caramel flavor here.  Good copper color too.  I kind of like this one.  Not my favorite pale ale but then again there really isnt anything wrong with it.  IF only I were a dodgers fan...
Best word to describe it is meh.  Only place Ive ever seen it is in Whole Foods, never at a liquor store.  Considering that, not too bad, but also not too good.
Good APA and a good hometown brew too.  Not sure if it is available nationwide.  Good color and nice floral aroma.
Very watery as you can probably tell just from looking at the color.  Definitely needs a lime wedge.

Not a great hefe but serviceable nevertheless.  There is a light citrus flavor that is enjoyable but not overpowering.  However, there really isnt too much that makes this one stand out from the crowd.

If it were an option I would give it all 0s.  Absolutely the worst beer, well lets not offend the rest of beer by calling it that, worst liquid that has ever gone down my throat.  Watery with a horrible, not only that but offensive after taste.  Worst of all, low alcohol so you have to drink a gallon of it to forget the piss that youre drinking.  AVOID AT ALL COSTS.  If youre on a diet for gods sake dont drink this.  Drink water.

The champagne of beers is it?  Well, perhaps if you enjoy piss cheap champagne.  No aroma, little flavor, very watery, but hey its Miller.  Drinking it from a keg probably didnt help these matters but i doubt i missed out on much anyway.

Miller once again delivers a lower quality beer.  Put back a few though and youll quickly forget not only who made it but also what it is that youre drinking.  Bottom line here, lots of alcohol for cheap.
Very driknable, expecially for a macrobrew.  Better than Budweiser and other similar crap, but definitely far from great

I wasnt necessarily expecting big things from this one, but I was pleasently surprised.  Nice bitter flavor.  Not something to drink frequently as you may tire of it but very nice for an occasional drink.
Definitely nothing wrong with this one.  I was expecting more from Sierra Nevada though since their Pale Ale is so good, so i was a little disappointed.
A decent APA.  Lots of hops but is balanced adequately with the malt so its not overpowering.  I wouldnt complain if i had it again, but there are other things i would buy for myself.
Distinct rye flavor, obviously look at the name, gives it a kind of bready flavor.  Not my favorite APA but still good and definitely worth a try.

I had heard good things about this one but to be honest i was a little disappointed.  More bitter than i expected and not a great finish.  Ill try it again probably since ive heard good things about it, but definitely better IPAs out there
This is definitely one of my favorite beers.  Not only is the flavor great, but you can find it pretty much anywhere.  Best APA Ive had
Not as good as regular Sam Adams in some respects, better in others.  On the whole Id rate them about the same.  There is a definite lemony flavor but its not too overpowering.
Among the most readily available American beers this has to be one of the best.  Not actually too bad in its own right for that matter.  Sure as hell better than Miller and the other mega breweries
